\f0\b\fs34 \cf2 1. Purpose of this Policy
\f1\b0\fs28 \
\
This Policy sets out the terms governing cancellations, refunds, credits, and rescheduling of services provided by Memorial Flight Co Pty Ltd trading as Memorial Flight Co Pty Ltd (
\f2\b Memorial Flight Co
\f1\b0 , 
\f2\b we
\f1\b0 , 
\f2\b us
\f1\b0 , or 
\f2\b our
\f1\b0 ).\
\
This Policy forms part of our Terms and Conditions. In the event of any inconsistency, this Policy prevails in relation to cancellation, refund, and rescheduling matters.\
\

\f0\b\fs34 2. Nature of the Service
\f1\b0\fs28 \
\
Our services involve the coordination of aircraft, pilots, airspace access, logistics, handling, scheduling, and operational planning.\
\
Once a Booking is accepted and scheduled, resources are allocated specifically to that Booking. For this reason, cancellation and refund rights are limited.\
\

\f0\b\fs34 3. When a Booking is Confirmed
\f1\b0\fs28 \
\
A Booking is considered confirmed when:\
\
a. we issue an Order Confirmation; and\
b. full payment has been received (unless otherwise agreed in writing).\
\
Once a Booking is confirmed, this Policy applies.\
\

\f0\b\fs34 4. Client Cancellation
\f1\b0\fs28 \
\
\pard\tx560\tx1120\tx1680\tx2240\tx2800\tx3360\tx3920\tx4480\tx5040\tx5600\tx6160\tx6720\sl324\slmult1\pardirnatural\partightenfactor0

\f0\b\fs30 \cf2 4.1 General rule
\f1\b0\fs28 \cf2 \
\
Except as required by law, 
\f2\b Bookings are non-refundable once confirmed
\f1\b0 .\
\
By proceeding with a Booking, the Client acknowledges that:\
\
a. the Service is time-sensitive and operationally scheduled;\
b. aircraft time, staff, and resources are allocated in advance; and\
c. cancellation may not be practicable without loss.\
\

\f0\b\fs30 \cf2 4.2 Cancellation before scheduling
\f1\b0\fs28 \cf2 \
\
If a Client requests cancellation 
\f2\b before the Service has been scheduled
\f1\b0 , we may, at our discretion:\
\
a. offer a partial refund;\
b. issue a credit; or\
c. deduct reasonable administrative, processing, and third-party costs.\
\
We are not obligated to provide a refund in these circumstances.\
\

\f0\b\fs30 \cf2 4.3 Cancellation after scheduling
\f1\b0\fs28 \cf2 \
\
Once a Service has been scheduled:\
\
a. no refund will be provided; and\
b. cancellation requests will generally not be accepted.\
\
We may, at our discretion, allow rescheduling in limited circumstances (see Section 6).\
\
