\f0\b\fs34 \cf2 10. Refusal or Cancellation by Memorial Flight Co
\f1\b0\fs28 \
\
We may refuse or cancel a Booking if:\
\
a. we cannot verify authority or identity;\
b. the Service would be unlawful or unsafe;\
c. required documentation is not provided;\
d. packaging or delivery requirements are not met;\
e. there is a dispute regarding the Cremated Remains;\
f. incorrect or misleading information has been provided; or\
g. operational or regulatory constraints prevent performance.\
\
In such cases:\
\
a. we may retain reasonable costs incurred; and\
b. any refund will be determined at our discretion, except where required by law.\
\

\f0\b\fs34 11. Partial Services and Deliverables
\f1\b0\fs28 \
\
If part of the Service has been performed, or resources have been committed, we may:\
\
a. retain all or part of the fees paid; and\
b. deduct reasonable costs associated with work already completed.\
\
If a supplementary deliverable (such as a certificate or video) cannot be provided due to technical issues, any refund is limited to the portion of the fee specifically attributable to that deliverable.\
\

\f0\b\fs34 12. Credits
\f1\b0\fs28 \
\
Where we elect to provide a credit:\
\
a. credits may be issued instead of refunds;\
b. credits may be subject to expiry;\
c. credits may be non-transferable unless otherwise stated; and\
d. credits may only be used for services offered by us.\
\

\f0\b\fs34 13. Australian Consumer Law
\f1\b0\fs28 \
\
Nothing in this Policy excludes, restricts, or modifies any rights or remedies you may have under the Australian Consumer Law or any other applicable law.\
\
Where a service fails to meet a consumer guarantee that cannot be excluded, you may be entitled to a remedy as provided by law.\
\

\f0\b\fs34 14. How to request a cancellation or reschedule
\f1\b0\fs28 \
\
All requests must be made in writing using the contact details provided in our Terms and Conditions or on our website.\
\
Requests must include:\
\
a. Client name;\
b. Booking reference;\
c. details of the request; and\
d. supporting information if relevant.\
\
We will respond within a reasonable time.\
\

\f0\b\fs34 15. Changes to this Policy
\f1\b0\fs28 \
\
We may update this Policy from time to time.\
\
The version published on our website at the time of your Booking will generally apply to that Booking unless a change is required by law.\
